I’m looking into mercaptoalcohols and noticing they can have strong odors like onion or garlic, along with sulfurous and meaty notes. Interesting that longer chains become less pungent and lean towards grapefruit or citrus smells. I'm considering 3-mercaptoheptanol and its naming ambiguity. Without position specificity, I wonder if "mercaptoheptanol" typically refers to something like 1-mercapto-2-heptanol. I’ll also check the descriptors used in fragrance databases to understand its scent better.', type='summary_text')
